Review Text: Ordered thali combo from zomato. Taste is good but quantity of curries they gave is less. Roties are also good. Plastic boxes can be avoided in the packing for curries.

I was visiting Hyderabad. I fell ill(flu). I needed some homely food as i could not eat more biryani or paneer-naan. I went to Gujarati mess. The fulka thali (Combo2) for 3 days, and i felt much better. The price they take for food is near social service. Keep on the good work.

Food was good quality and felt like I was eating home made food... request restaurant to add extra methi paratha or phulka on add on basis so that we can order extra roti along with the combos.. I have ordered methi paratha thali and was hoping for a nice homely authentic meal but sadly was very disappointed.

Please do not disappoint customer on the cuisine that you are offering. Try being little authentic.

This is a 2BHK flat converted into a restaurant. The place is very simple so much that you need to throw your own plates. The food like most reviews say is very simple and homely. Rotis are served hot which is great. However the variety is missing.Moreover the menu that you find here on Zomato isn't the same available in the restaurant. Just the name is Gujarati Mess and the items in the thali aren't. Maybe I expected a lot from this place. Further the owner isn't quite a jovial person and you cannot strike a conversation with him. Simple, no frills yet tasty food. You can have food here on regular basis. It's place to go when our kitchen is closed, and yet you want homely food. Staff is courteous. Since it is 'mess', you surely can't expect great ambiance but it's kept quite clean. Lastly you are expected to put your plate in sink after food (Just like in United States of Gujarat :) ).

Great place for daily meal. Phulkas are better than most other places. Curry are not too spicy and tastes like home. You get option of smaller meal if you are not too hungry. Have aloo paratha and methi paratha as option which serves as change in case you are bored with rotis. Sweets and lassi are available to soothe your mood. Overall, great meal at moderate cost.
